# - use enumerate to get index and value of a list
# - sys.exit(0) means a clean exit without any errors / problems
# - sys.exit(1) means there was some issue / error / problem and that is why the program is exiting.
# - this is not Python specific and is pretty common.
# - use boolean variables to keep track of a specific state / condition

